Course
 on selected topics in legal history. Spring 2013 Topic: readings and 
discussions on Supreme Court cases addressing freedom of speech; 
discrimination on basis of race, gender, and sexual orientation; 
congressional and presidential power, and rights of the accused. 
Requires two short papers and a longer final paper.

